race.comment: Tricky race to end the day. THEY CALL ME DUSTY (5) has been doing all his recent racing at this track and, while his winning strike rate is poor, he has run a couple of decent races. He maps to get a nice run midfield and can be finishing hard. At the price, he looks an each-way play. MISS REMSKI (3) is a winner at her only start here and her overall form looks better than most of her rivals. She's drawn to get a cosy run and can fight out the finish. LAST DREAM (8) won well on the heavy track last start and shapes as a key runner again, especially if the track remains wet. Including MR GEORGE (1) and TOES IN FIRST (2) in quaddies and exotics.
